7 PART IV. REPEAL OF RURAL HEALTH CARE STABILIZATION PROGRAM
8 SECTION 4.1. Article 2 of Chapter 131A of the General Statutes, with the exception
9 of G.S. 131A-32, as recodified and amended by Part I of this act, is repealed.
10
11 PART V. TRANSFERS AND APPROPRIATIONS
12 SECTION 5.1. Effective July 1, 2026, the entire unrestricted cash balance of the
13 Rural Health Care Stabilization Fund within the Office of State Budget and Management (Budget
14 Code 23018) is transferred to the Rural Healthcare Infrastructure Fund created by G.S. 131E-74,
15 as enacted by Section 1.1(b) of this act. The funds transferred are appropriated for the fiscal year
16 in which they are transferred. Any remaining principal and interest payments due to the Rural
17 Health Care Stabilization Fund on or after July 1, 2026, shall be paid to the Rural Healthcare
18 Infrastructure Fund.
19 SECTION 5.2. Notwithstanding G.S. 131E-74(c), as enacted by Section 1.1(b) of
20 this act, there is appropriated from the Rural Healthcare Infrastructure Fund to the Department
21 of Health and Human Services, Division of Central Management and Support, Office of Rural
22 Health, the sum of one million dollars ($1,000,000) in nonrecurring funds to fund a contract with
23 Rural Healthcare Initiative, Inc., a nonprofit organization, to continue the work funded by S.L.
24 2023-134 involving the creation of effective models of sustainable healthcare for North Carolina
25 rural communities; to develop cost estimates for achieving the healthcare facilities described in
26 these initial models of sustainable healthcare; and to support the work of the North Carolina Rual
27 Healthcare Infrastructure Council and the Office of Rural Health in developing a plan for the
28 establishment and administration of a Rural Healthcare Infrastructure Program funded by the
29 Rural Healthcare Infrastructure Fund created by G.S. 131E-74, as enacted by Section 1.1(b) of
30 this act.
31
32 PART VI. EFFECTIVE DATE
33 SECTION 6.1. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective July 1, 2026.
